article.description: — Orlando Robinson had 22 points as Fresno State easily defeated Weber State 69-43 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Robinson scores 22 to lift Fresno State over Weber State
article.linkText: Robinson scores 22 to lift Fresno State over Weber State
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- — Orlando Robinson had 22 points as Fresno State easily defeated Weber State 69-43 on Thursday night. Anthony Holland had 10 points for Fresno State (10-3). Isaiah Hill added six assists and Leo Colimerio had eight rebounds. Fresno State dominated the first half and led 44-18 at halftime. Jamison Overton had 12 points for the Wildcats (9-4). Koby McEwen added 10 points and eight rebounds, and Dillon Jones had 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
